# Rule: CHANGELOG.md

`CHANGELOG.md` follows [keep-a-changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/)
style. Each version section is added by the PR that ships the
phase.

A version section must:

- be in chronological order (newest at the top);
- list the component(s) shipped (cite `SPEC.md` rows);
- list the ADR(s) shipped (cite `docs/adr/NNNN-…`);
- list the user‑visible changes under `### Added`,
  `### Changed`, `### Deprecated`, `### Removed`, `### Fixed`,
  `### Security` as relevant;
- link to the PR (if known) and to the diff (compare‑view URL);
- stay under ~120 lines total (older versions are kept terse).

The first version (the bootstrap) is `0.1.0`. The next version,
shipping the first real component, is `0.2.0`.

## Template

```markdown
# Changelog

All notable changes to this project are documented in this file.
The format follows [keep-a-changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/).

## [0.2.0] — YYYY-MM-DD

PR: <URL or "not yet">

### Added

- Component: **Supervisor** (`SPEC.md` row). ADR: `docs/adr/NNNN-<slug>.md`.

## [0.1.0] — 2026-07-10

PR: <URL>

### Added

- Initial bootstrap: monorepo, governance, skill layer. See
  `AGENTS.md` and `.agents/`.
```